summary: In a surprising turn of events at the Paris 2024 Olympic opener, Nigeria's women's basketball team defeated the Australian Opals, who were heavily favored to win. Nigeria's triumph shook the basketball world, as they outplayed the Australians in three-point shooting under the leadership of Kayla Alexander. Unfortunately, Australia suffered a setback when Bec Allen sustained a hamstring injury in the final warm-up game, ruling her out of the Olympics.
